This paper deals with the application of cognitive psychology to improve user interfaces of applications that use concept hierarchies. It proposes a method to identify basic level concepts within a hierarchy, which can be useful for classification tasks. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
